Your Honor,

I am Aleksander Nowak, and I stand before you today to express my plea of guilty to the charge of assault. I take full responsibility for my actions and deeply regret the harm I caused.

During a moment of intense anger, I pushed my employee to the ground and proceeded to kick him in the stomach. I recognize that my violent behavior was inexcusable, regardless of the mistake he made at work. I allowed my emotions to overpower my better judgment, and I deeply regret succumbing to such violence.

Immediately after the incident, I acted swiftly and transported the victim to the closest emergency room to ensure he received the necessary medical attention. I understand the pain and distress that my actions have caused both the victim and his family, and I extend my heartfelt apologies to them.

Your Honor, I stand before you today with genuine remorse for my actions. I recognize the gravity of my mistake and the suffering it has caused. I assure the court that this incident is not indicative of my true character. I am committed to learning from this experience and taking the necessary steps to ensure that I never engage in such reprehensible behavior again.

Thank you for considering the circumstances surrounding this case, Your Honor. I am fully aware of the seriousness of the situation and prepared to face the consequences of my actions.
